body:
@emilianbold I see you're trying to break a deadlock when a `ModuleInstall` calls back to the system. What if the the special handling would apply to just the length of execution of `ModuleInstall.closing` called from `ModuleManager` ? I.e. some thread-local would help.

Not ideal as it does not prevent exits called from async tasks waited on. WARN log is a good idea anyway.

Instead of return, the exit() could throw some nasty kind of exception that would cut through caller's code and gets caught in the `NbInstaller`  loop: it will return a sort of, but unless the caller does some error handling it will break out of the code more cleanly than a `return` that is not documented.
